Symmetry Test for Polar Graphs
) 1. Symmetry about the x-axis: If the point ( ,r θ lies on the graph, then the point ( , r θ − ) or ( r − ,πθ− ) lies on the graph.
) , 2. Symmetry about the y-axis: If the point ( ,r θ lies on the graph, then the point ( ,r πθ− ) or ( r θ−− ) lies on the graph.
) 3. Symmetry about the origin: If the point ( ,r θ lies on the graph, then the point ( r− ,θ ) or ( ,r θ π + ) lies on the graph.
